Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the expressive power of higher-order calculi, which is a topic closely related to logic.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the expressive power of probabilistic choice operators in a calculus.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with probabilistic distributions and their properties.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper discusses the representation of functions in different calculi.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper deals with the complexity of probabilistic higher-order calculi.
